Label: The Lancet
description: For two centuries, The Lancet has sought to address urgent topics in our society, initiate debate, put science into context, and influence decision makers around the world. Today the Lancet family of journals publishes leading research across the full spectrum of clinical and global health, retaining at its core the belief that medicine must serve society, that knowledge must transform society, that the best science must lead to better lives. Videos on this channel reveal details of research, empower authors to present their work in their own words, and explore the implications of key developments in science and health. Video abstracts and clinical picture videos showcase researchers giving succinct summaries of critical research or striking clinical cases, while features on recent research or our journals themselves invite you to consider how the advancement and sharing of knowledge can transform society. Label: Kings and Generals
description: Welcome to Kings and Generals, the premier YouTube channel for anyone interested in military history. Our channel is dedicated to providing high-quality educational content that explores some of the most significant military campaigns, battles, and strategies throughout history. From the ancient world to the modern era, we cover a wide range of topics with a focus on in-depth analysis and informative discussions. Our videos feature detailed maps, graphics, and animations that bring historical events to life and make them easier to understand. Kings and Generals is the go-to resource for anyone looking to learn more about military history. Join our community of history enthusiasts and discover the fascinating world of military history with Kings and Generals. Sponsorship email: info@kingsandgenerals.net

Label: Matt Whitman
description: I'm Matt and I'm endlessly curious about the Bible and Christianity and the God those things are about. I was raised around Evangelical Christianity, collected a few degrees about theology and such, pastored churches and then had my faith fall apart. I spent time believing there was no God, but then started over on Christian faith from the beginning, and that's where I am now. The idea of an infinite God setting out to redeem a busted up but still beautiful world over the long haul is about the most interesting thing I can imagine, and that (at its core) is what all my videos are about. I make explainer videos, do reviews, tour churches, interview people, make deep-dive history and theology stuff and sometimes I post ridiculous sketches. Feel free to enjoy what you resonate with and ignore the rest. If you're here, it's because your curiosity overlaps with mine, and I'm grateful for that. I'm always glad to cross paths with anyone of good will whether we agree on everything or not.

Label: Alliterative
description: I'm a university prof with a PhD in Medieval Studies. I use language, literature, and history to explore the web of connections in the world around us. Many of the videos on this channel start with a word as a jumping off point, with its history and etymology opening up a way to explore history and culture more widely. Others examine literary devices, cognitive science, myth, medieval literature, history of science, and a wide variety of other topics. The "endless knot" is a common visual motif of an interconnected knot with no beginning or end, found in many cultures around the world. My use of the symbol is a reference to the 14th c. poem "Sir Gawain & the Green Knight", where it describes the pentangle which Gawain has emblazoned on his shield as a symbol of the interconnectedness of things. Here it also gains significance from its comparison to the cognitive science hexagram or heptagram which shows the interrelated nature of various fields in cognitive science.

Label: CompChomp
description: I'm Jessica. I code and I byte! CHOMP! We're going to explore all the amazing ways computer code touches your life every day. Hehee, touches... Anyways. Here are some coding-meets-life questions I want to nibble at. - Is AI already breeding humans? - How do videogame developers deceive you into thinking your game is more advanced than it really is? - Are programming languages really languages? - How do Star Wars droids hack and get hacked? - Why is there still a lack of female developers? Josh from NativLang is doing all the fun animations. We're even working on a collaboration about the overlap between linguistics and programming languages - why passwords aren't words, how Cold War machines failed at translating Russian.... ooh, this is gonna be fun! Dubba CHOMP!

Label: The Virtual Linguistics Campus
description: The educational videos in this channel (complete list: https://bit.ly/2YRk5yD) are interconnected with the E-Learning units on the Virtual Linguistics Campus (https://oer-vlc.de) , the E-Learning platform for linguistics hosted by Prof. Handke's award winning Linguistic Engineering Team of Marburg University, Germany, but can also be used as stand-alone instructional videos. The early videos were produced in a classroom-setting, since 2015, we have applied an office-setting using an ActivBoard or a green screen and Camtasia Studio. And our presentation strategy? It is essential for us that in E-Lectures you always see your lecturer. Instead of reading off without being visible and presenting our content in a sterile way, we can be watched while lecturing - with all our mistakes and weaknesses - but that's the human factor, isn't it? The Micro-Lectures, by contrast, due to their brevity and conciseness do not involve a talking head.

Label: Keith Fenner
description: I'm Keith Fenner and this is my Job Shop. Join me as I perform old school repair jobs by drilling, milling, grinding, welding, plasma cutting, broaching and metalworking on a lathe. At Turn Wright Machine Works, we walk the talk and getter done! After school, I started my career in naval ship repair as an outside machinist working as a civilian contractor at the helper level. 13.5 years later I had worked on almost every navy vessel in San Diego's harbor, 32nd Street, North Island and Point Loma. I added the classification of an inside machinist to my cap, and the capability of holding any personnel level in the work force. After that I worked for two small companies that I helped to grow. In return, I gained my welding and shafting experience, before eventually taking a leave of absence to start my own business in 1994 - Turn Wright Machine Works - homesteading my talents here on Cape Cod.

Karena pendidikan itu memberdayakan. Anda akan belajar tentang gangguan bipolar, depresi, kecemasan, gangguan defisit perhatian, skizofrenia dan banyak lagi. Saya mengelompokkan video untuk topik ini ke dalam daftar putar. Youtube memungkinkan Anda untuk menyimpan daftar putar ke perpustakaan Anda. Jika Anda hanya tertarik pada satu topik, Anda dapat menyimpan daftar putar dan melihat kapan video baru tentang topik tersebut dipublikasikan. Penafian -Semua informasi adalah untuk tujuan pendidikan dan tidak dimaksudkan sebagai saran medis khusus/pribadi dari saya untuk Anda. Jika Anda memiliki dokter sendiri, mungkin video ini dapat membantu mempersiapkan Anda untuk berdiskusi dengan dokter Anda.

Label: Gameplay and Talk
description: Retro gaming playthroughs/walkthroughs and live streams that are gameplay-focused, covering various mechanics and other helpful tips throughout each playthrough. My dedicated videos are guided playthroughs done live on the spot, with some light editing highlighting various talking points and game mechanics. These are meant to show the game from start to finish and aim to help new players get comfortable with any given title. I also occasionally host live streams. Sometimes they are of the "Variety" type, showing off a bunch of games for a single platform, or more focused ones where I try to play a longer game in a single sitting (or two). I play a bit of everything but my tastes lean towards classic 2D platformers, first-person shooters, shoot 'em ups (shmups) and other action games. You can expect to see content geared towards that more often than not. I am also a big fan of Castlevania and Doom, so expect to see those featured regularly. Thanks for checking out my channel!

Label: Denise Soden
description: Hello everyone! My name is Denise Soden. I am a wildlife watercolorist, educational content creator, and pigment nerd located in Salem, Oregon. I've been captivated by both art and animals since before I can remember. I began drawing as soon as I could hold a crayon and spent my second birthday at a local zoo where I would later become the education manager. I also spent much of my young adult life as a hobbyist photographer, and in 2013, I fulfilled my lifelong dream of traveling to Botswana to photograph the some of the most amazing animals that we share our planet with. I now take that love for wildlife and share it through watercolor as a full time artist and content creator. In addition to YouTube, I create casual, real-time tutorials on Patreon and professional, detailed classes on Skillshare. I also have custom watercolor palettes available with Da Vinci Paint Co. located in the United States.

Label: warwick TCS
description: HEY THERE! Do you call more than one country 'home'? Have you attended an international school? Are you an expat? If so, you might not know it but you're a Third Culture Kid! WarwickTCS, a society within the University of Warwick (UK), aims to unite those that are part of a Third Culture: individuals who have spent a significant amount of time outside of their parents' culture, are not fully connected to one culture but multiple ones, and ultimately share their sense of belonging with others of similar backgrounds. Check out our official YouTube account for travel vlogs, culture vlogs, interviews on what it means to be a TCK and other TCK-related videos! Don't forget to subscribe :)

Label: Rupert Powell
description: The Ramblings of a telescope maker... 15 years ago my Father bought me a 1940's Myford lathe. I didn't really know what to make with it, other than chips! I had always been interested in Astronomy and had a cheap Chinese telescope but decide to set about making my own refracting telescope. Once I made this I was bitten by the bug and have now made several telescopes and associated astronomical instruments. One of my scopes has even been featured on the BBC's The Sky at Night program. (check out my website for a link). I now have a full workshop with a Harrison M300 lathe and a Bridgeport Series 1 milling machine. I started making Youtube videos to show customers how their parts were made, but now enjoy it in its own right.

Label: Quantum Light TV
description: They train us in the medical field not to think of children as small adults because their bodies react differently to situations than adults do and their bodies aren't in the same shape or proportions as adults. We are told to think of them as small, misshapen adults. So it is in nature. Small things don't behave the same as objects we're use to interacting with on a regular basis. In fact, on the quantum level behavior can begin to seem so bizarre that it seems all reason, logic and intuition must be thrown out the window. This fascinates me. With the plethora of information available to even the most amateur hobbyist, I think we can have a lot of fun discussing, experimenting and demonstrating some many wonderful things in the quantum by simply using light.
